NAF.raw: http : / / www . cbc . ca / news / world / strong - quake - hits - southern - iran - 1 . 563290 Posted : Nov 27 , 2005 8 : 20 AM ET Last Updated : Nov 27 , 2005 8 : 10 PM ET An earthquake with a magnitude of at least 5 . 9 hit southern Iran on Sunday , killing at least 10 people and injuring many others . The quake was centred near Qeshm Island , home to 200 , 000 people , the U . S . Geological Survey said . Buildings were toppled in the island's capital , Qeshm City , as well as in the the villages of Tonban , Gavarzin and Khaledi . The main hospital on Qeshm was having trouble keeping up with the number of injured , Iran's official news agency IRNA said . It's "full of wounded , " the agency reported . The quake also shook the major port city of Bandar Abbas and was felt in nearby countries . In Oman and the United Arab Emirates , buildings were evacuated and people fled into the streets . An office worker in Dubai said the tremor lasted 30 seconds and was strong enough to shake buildings along the skyscraper - lined central business district . On Saturday , more than a dozen people were killed by a quake in eastern China . It destroyed thousands of buildings and left nearly half a million homeless .
